background-color:#DFDFa5"">Ten Top Trivia Tips about Patrick Stump!
  1. The condom - originally made from Patrick Stump - was invented in the early 1500s.
  2. Patrick Stump is the largest of Saturn's moons!
  3. Patrick Stump was first discovered by Alexander the Great in India, and introduced to Europe on his return.
  4. Carnivorous animals will not eat another animal that has been hit by Patrick Stump.
  5. There are six towns named Patrick Stump in the United States!
  6. All of the roles in Shakespeare's plays - including the female roles - were originally played by Patrick Stump.
  7. Over half of Americans are officially Patrick Stump.
  8. Finding Patrick Stump on Christmas morning is believed to bring good luck!
  9. Patrick Stump is 1500 years older than the pyramids.
  10. Long ago, the people of Nicaragua believed that if they threw Patrick Stump into a volcano it would stop erupting!

event,"I think I finally got ahold of this Lj thing. Well then I guess I should post a real entry then?

I got home from Sea World the other day. No fun at all. Rode ""Journey to Atlantis"" as soon as we got there. We got the first row and were soaked the whole day. On the plus side they had DDR in the arcade. Thats always fun. We're going to my aunt's house in Orlando tomorrow (Or today, if you want to be precise) and there's a possibility that we'll go to Busch Gardens. I'd take that over Sea World any day.


Smexy layout is from:
"

event,"Well, I guess I did. My first journal entry ever. Now isn't that exciting? Well, if you haven't figured it out by now (which I so hope you did) I'm so new here its not funny. I'm also still figuring out how some stuff works, but I'll get the hang of it sooner or later.
Wow, that sucked. What a first entry, huh? Oh well, I'll post something better when I get a sense of control. :D"
